parameters: This is my first time seeing one.
Wow! This place looks like a cabin with a field over there...
You came back a little earlier than usual, \C[5]Maleena\c[0].
Who is this little one? Is he your new friend?
I was jumping off a tree and...
landed my foot... on his face...
I brought him here because I was worried that he would get any injuries.
Can you check on him for me?
There are a few small scratches on the face.
This is my homemade medicine with natural herbs.
It will heal scratches on your face.
How did you do that, kid?
I felt a sudden gust of wind slap my face and my body immediately pulled back on its own.
If you master it, you will be as slippery as a fish.
No one can land a punch on you.
Why are you touching my arms and legs?
I'm just doing some exercise and stretching.
You are a bit old to learn martial arts but you have many things that can make you a great fighter.
I can teach you, Muay Thai. My homeland fighting style.
Do you want to be my student?
It's boring and takes a lot of time!
But you can fight bad buddies and many girls will fall in love with you.
I will teach you for free.
We are not in an action movie.
And I have more important things to do.
Okay, you just missed your chance.
It will be kinda pricey if you want to learn something from me.
He turns his face like flipping paper.
Guess you really do have a pair.
Was that... supposed to be a compliment?
It was sarcasm. Let’s get started.
show me what \C[20]Grandpa Ek\c[0]’s taught you so far.
I mean... I’ve survived so far?
Not the flex you think it is. Come on, stance up.
Lucky for you, I’m feeling generous.
You're not bracing for a school photo.
Now your core—this needs to stay active.
Your center needs to be firm.
Guard your jaw, not your chest.
There. Now you almost look like someone I wouldn’t instantly knock out.
You kicked like you were trying to swat a bug with your shin.
It’s hard with you watching me like a hawk.
You’ll get used to it. Or you’ll cry.
Alright. Break time. But don’t think we’re done.
Next time, I go full speed. Maybe.
I feel both excited... and doomed.

I thought you didn't want to do boring things.
You won't get anything from this old man.
They call me the helper boy.
I wouldn't do this every day, tho.
Little force is better than nothing.
But I won't give you anything for your help.
Thanks for your help, little one.
Do you know where I can buy a stage for photoshoots?
Buy? Hmm, not that I know of.
But I do have a set of blueprints for building a stage.
for the low low price of \c[17]2000\c[0]\i[172]!
It's a bit expensive because it's quite complex.

The Mysterious Ritual and Rank System
Starting to think you might actually enjoy this.
I still miss my bed every time I walk out here.
The path to strength ain’t made of pillows.
Fighting’s not about rage. It’s about rhythm.
Lose the beat, lose the fight.
I always thought strength came from emotion...
You feel something strange in the air lately?
The forest whispers when it's uneasy.
Even the birds are acting weird.
Not yet. Just don’t ignore it.
But she used to cry when the chickens pecked her.
They had evil in their eyes!
So this is why she always gives the chickens the side-eye...
She used to cry when chickens pecked her.
Now look at her — bending the earth like it’s nothing.
Makes me proud... and a little scared.
She strong. But strength isn’t all she needs.
Remind her it’s okay to lean on people.
You like her, don’t you? Heh. Don’t mess it up.
She’ll break you... emotionally and physically.
You think you can waltz in, throw a few punches, and ask about her?
You’re going to sit under that and not fall.
Control your body. Control your breath. Control yourself.
Don’t block the water—stand with it.
Picture your energy like a flame.
Just a spark... in the right place.
Power’s not about breaking everything in your path.
It’s about knowing when not to.
You feel it—power coiling beneath your skin.*
Slam your whole weight into a devastating forward kick!
Wait—seriously? I showed up early and everything.
Proceed with Ek's story to access it.\c[0]
Can I sit here and watch your training?
But give it everything you’ve got tomorrow.
You are not my student anyway.
I shouldn't have refused so quickly.
I don't think you're still sitting here.
Thank you for letting me observe.
Let’s see if you’re tougher than last time.
Same deal — knock ‘em down, clean ‘em up.
Don't make me regret trusting you.

You’re always up before the sun, huh?
You ever wake up sore and still want to train?
Now stop talking and hold that stance before \C[20]Grandpa Ek\c[0] throws a chair.
Last time your leg almost took out the weapons rack.
Hey, that was a dynamic warm-up.
That was a near-death experience for \C[20]Grandpa Ek\c[0]’s favorite spear.
I used to train alone every morning.
Let’s not get sloppy just because we’re... closer.
I want you to be strong — not just soft.
Training with someone who knows me like that.
You mean who’s seen you naked?
But mostly... someone who shows up.
Didn’t scare you off last time?
Please—I’ve been mentally preparing all day.
Tighten your core. Lift your guard higher.
You're leaving your whole side open.
Maybe I’m just giving you a free shot?
Tempting. But I’ll wait until you earn it.
You’re starting to look like you know what you’re doing.
Launch upward and smash down with brutal force!
Crush through defenses with a savage, bone-breaking knee!
A single, focused strike meant to break anything foolish enough to stand!
Think you could show me a few moves?
Hmm... asking for training before even joining the dojo?
I can't even see his hand.
This is nothing compared to when I was younger.
I can chop all these logs in one minute.
Does material arts training make people that strong?
You said I come here for the Bee House solutions.
We will talk about it later after I've finished all of this.
The most important thing if you want to build anything.
Go to the desired location and place it.
How can I make a Bee House "Scroll"?
Before that you need a Blueprint.
You can buy it from me, here.
After gathering all the necessary Materials listed in the Blueprint, you can go to your Workbench and use all of those to create a final product.
The basic materials are Wood, Stone and Nails.
I have to go to the forest to chop trees now?
You can only do that if you have a logging license.
you can get wood from cutting those.
Only choose the \c[1]Bluish Stones\c[0], they contains some iron elements which will make the structure more solid.
You can buy those from me as well but it has a really high price.
I could build a solid gold house with those materials money.
Then the only way you can go now is to find them by yourself.
I'm the only one selling wood and stone in this town.
It will be more fun by doing it yourself, little one.
Oh! I still have something for you.
An axe from my great, great grandfather.
It's in a bad condition and I can't use it anymore.
Better give it to someone than throw it away.
There's only one blacksmith in town.
I have some business with her before.
You can buy \c[1]Nails\c[0] and \c[1]Hammer\c[0] from her too.
collect all the \c[1]Necessary Materials\c[0] listed in the blueprint then go to the \c[1]Workingbench\c[0]...
Choose the \c[1]Desired Location\c[0] and place the \c[1]Final Product\c[0].
I can get \c[1]Wood\c[0] and \c[1]Stone\c[0] from chopping \c[1]Tree Stumps\c[0] and mashing \c[1]Bluish Rocks\c[0].
But first I need to place the \c[1]Workbench\c[0] first.
There's a small area near my Planting Spot.
You've learned how to build a \c[14]Bee House

Damn... I should’ve accepted it already.
Not sure if it still counts.
Hm? You delivering milk or just lost again?
No. I want you to train me.
So the city boy finally wants to throw hands, huh?
I need to get stronger. For real this time.
Every fool with a bruised ego says the same thing.
Doesn’t mean they can stick around once their knuckles start bleeding.
Let’s see if your spine backs them up.
You want me to train you?
Then start by doing what most can't—listen. And follow orders.
Not whining when I tell you to carry buckets or chase chickens.
And I will tell you that.
That’s not exactly the training I imagined...
No one imagines greatness begins with hauling slop and digging holes.
Then be here at dawn. Not a minute late.
And bring your patience—you're gonna hate it.
So you finally gave in, huh?
Be ready—he won’t go easy on you just ‘cause you’re new.
He made me carry rocks uphill for a week.
You’ll be sleeping with them by the end of today.
But seriously, I’m glad you’re doing this...
It’s hard, but it’s worth it.
Put your full force into that kick,

I can’t wait to start my first real training!
You really thought today was about fancy footwork?
First, you're going to build the muscles that carry the fight.
Come on—banana grove. Time to work.
Not bad... not bad at all.
You've put in the work. Stronger. Smarter.
Still got a dumb face—but hey, we can’t fix everything.
I didn’t realize I’ve changed so much...)
Are you ready to dedicate yourself fully to this path?
Hah... there it is. That fire in your eyes.
Now I can start whooping you into shape too.
From today forward—you’re not just a worker.
Make me proud... or regret it.
Alright. Let’s see what those legs can really do.
Try a sweeping low kick. Hit it like you mean it.
That all you got? Then go home.
You came here for strength, and this is what you bring?
What did you come here for, \n[1]?
(To protect. To rise. To be better.)
Geez, you could’ve warned me before you broke him.
You really pushed past your limit.
It kinda feels like I kicked past it.
You nearly knocked the whole post loose.
...You didn’t give up. That’s what matters.
Would’ve been easier if you weren’t watching.
Hey, I had to make sure you didn’t pass out dramatically.
You gonna go easy on me?

Of course I did. I’ve been waiting all night for this!
Good. Then let’s begin your real lesson.
Today, you stop being a rock... and start becoming a chain.
A chain is only strong when every link moves together.
Fists, feet, hips, core—it all flows as one.
I thought it was supposed to be more like... water?
Sure. If your goal is to gently hydrate your opponent.
You? You need to hit like a damn whip.
It’s rhythm. Timing. Control. I can do that.)
Drive your hips and heel through the line,
tear through the target like a whipping chain!
Not bad. You’re a quick learner.
But don’t let it get to your head. That was step one.
And you nearly lost your balance on the follow-through.
Right... still a lot to work on.
You’ve got potential—but potential doesn’t win fights.
That wasn’t perfect.. but it felt good.)
Come back tomorrow, and we’ll really begin.
